title.narrative: Support to the National Education Pact Project

description.narrative: The objective of the Project is to improve the Borrower&rsquo;s capacity to: (i) recruit and train primary and secondary school teachers, (ii) assess student learning in primary and secondary education, (iii) evaluate the quality of service provided by Public Early Childhood Development Centers, and (iv) enhance the process for decentralizing public school management.&nbsp;

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Institutional Arrangement | Description :The Borrower shall maintain during the implementation of the Project,OCI, IDEICE, INAIPI, INABIE, INAFOCAM, INEFI, ISFODOSU, and any other relevant entities necessary for implementing the Project, allwith powers, functions, capacity, staffing, terms of reference, and resources satisfactory to the Bank to fulfill their respectivefunctions under the Project, as set forth in the Operations Manual. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Other Undertakings | Description :The Borrower shall establish not later than February 28, 2016, and thereaftermaintain, a Project Steering Committee with composition consisting of, (i) a representative of OCI, (ii) a representative of theMINERD’s Vice-Ministry of Planning, (iii) a representative of the MINERD’s Vice-Ministry of Technical and Pedagogical Services, and(iv) a representative of the Borrower's Ministry of Finance. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS
